Before the Temple Gate~
The path from Chinatown gets thinner here and small cobblestones line the
road.  Large, broad leafed trees, and blossomed cherry trees form a barrier
between this place and the rest of Bal Harbour.  To the north lies the
Temple, sanctuary from the twisted, banality-ridden reality that is the
'real' world.  
