#8802
Under the Arch~
The trees peel back here, to reveal a large Torii gate, a Shinto gateway
from the mundane to the sacred space of the Temple.  Large Bamboo poles form
a sort of tunnel, lined with inscriptions in Japanese characters.  The light
is dappled, at night shadows cast by large lanterns dance over the wood,
giving it an otherworldly feeling.  To the north lies the foyer of the
temple, and the entrance to the physical structure itself, and to the south
is the pathway leading back to chinatown.  
~
