#8803
The Temple Foyer~
The quiet sobriety of the Temple grounds is most evident here.  The room
is open, the halls to the tea rooms to the east or west, and the entrance to
the temple and the Torii gate to the south.  To the north lies the
centrepiece of the entire temple, The Elemental Gardens.  The walls of this
room are lined with waxed bamboo, the shadows again dancing and flickering
as the wind tugs at the flames of the candles around the room.  
~
